SIMPLE: worthily
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Worthily
<hw>Wor"thi*ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In a worthy
manner; excellently; deservedly; according to merit; justly; suitably;
becomingly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>You <qex>worthily</qex> succeed not only to the honors of your
ancestors, but also to their virtues.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Some may very <qex>worthily</qex> deserve to be hated.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Worthiness</ent>⟦br⟧
